SIMPLE: optative
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Optative
<hw>Op"ta*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>optativus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>optatif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Expressing
desire or wish.</def> <rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Optative mood</b></col> <fld>(Gram.)</fld>, <cd>that mood
or form of a verb, as in Greek, Sanskrit, etc., in which a wish or
desire is expressed.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Optative</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Optative
<hw>Op"ta*tive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>optatif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Something to be
desired.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>The optative mood; also, a verb
in the optative mood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Optatively</ent>⟦br⟧
